{
  "stem": "24111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Don't forget, at that time, mail service existed between the camp of Theresienstadt and the families in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got letters from people which were deported to Theresienstadt asking, for example, about-- about members in the family, and asking also if it would be possible to send them money, or send them food, which we didn't have anyway, but send them parcels.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Every letter was censored, which means it was opened and closed by a paper stripe from-- from the-- from the German authorities.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yet sometimes, when family members sent money to Theresienstadt, we knew from other letters returning that they got the money.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we knew about conditions in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Dachau and Buchenwald, also people were allowed to write a postcard a month and were allowed to receive a postcard back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we knew about certain conditions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They-- they were not able to tell us in words, 'we were beaten' or 'we were badly treated.' But they knew how to-- to write certain things and we knew how to read between lines.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we knew also that in Poland different camps existed, because out of certain camps, we never got any answers back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was no mail service to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We only heard rumors, unsubstantiated rumors.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But at that time, we rather started to believe those rumors.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because we knew how the Germans acted.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew how the people were treated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people which came back out of the concentration camps, like my cousin from Dachau, he told us certain things.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't tell anything-- he didn't wanted to go in much detail, but we-- we started to get the message.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I took it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I also asked him, very, very sincerely, Aron, please help me.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
